ownedComment.body: Each SW Unit can call the RFE HW function to set & get register fields in an efficient way.

Enumeration to be filled with register fields needed by each SW Unit by the respective SW Unit Designer.
This index will correspond to an entry in an internal rfeHw_fieldTable that contains all the required attributes to set/get each field efficiently.

beginMultiField(): Begins a new joint field update operation (set/get multiple fields in an efficient way) setMultiField(): Buffers a value to be written to the HW register field when calling commit function, after checking wether it is within MIN/MAX getMultiField(): Buffers a pointer to be written with the value from corresponding HW register field when calling commit function commitMultiField(): Executes all buffered set & get operations by reading/writing HW registers in an efficient way setSingleField(): Writes a value immediately to HW register field, after checking whether it is within MIN/MAX getSingleField(): Reads a value immediately from HW register field

Each SW Unit can call the RFE HW function to set & get register fields in an efficient way.

documentation.value: \brief This function will tune GLDO1V3 voltage and load a profile across the rfe. \details Workaround STRX-5557: Pre-tune GLDO1V3 voltage to avoid di/dt issue \param [in] chirpProfileIndex - Chirp profile index to load \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

properties.documentation: rfeHw_bandgapTrim_t holds bandgap DC and curvature trim bit settings.
rfeHw_trim3Bits_t holds 3-bit trim value, used e.g. in bandgap curvature trimming.

documentation.value: !< Bandgap curvature trim value, Note: default setting

properties.documentation: rfeHw_trim4bits_t holds 4-bit trim value, used e.g. for bandgap DC trimming.
This enumerated type defines the indices of units, used to address one of the same type of IP, e.g. one of the four TXs, or one of the four RXs, etc.

documentation.value: Special index for SPI multicast writing of a single value to a register in all IP instances, e.g. the 4 TXs or 4 RXs. !!!Warning: It will set the register of each TX or Rx to an identical value.

properties.documentation: This enumeration type defines selections of PPD VGA gain.
